article.description: Tramaine Isabell scored a career-high 35 points and grabbed 13 rebounds to lead Drexel to an 89-77 victory over Rider on Saturday.
article.headline: Isabell scores 35 points, leads Drexel over Rider 89-77
article.linkText: Isabell scores 35 points, leads Drexel over Rider 89-77
article.story: PHILADELPHIA -- Tramaine Isabell scored a career-high 35 points and grabbed 13 rebounds to lead Drexel to an 89-77 victory over Rider on Saturday. Isabell was 11 of 18 from the floor and made four 3-pointers. Sammy Mojica added 22 points on 7-of-14 shooting and Austin Williams chipped in 12 points for Drexel (4-4). Tyere Marshall scored 23 points and Dimencio Vaughn had 20 to lead Rider (5-3). Frederick Scott and Jordan Allen added 10 points apiece. The Dragons took the lead for good, 56-53, and stretched it to double digits with 7:10 to play. Marshall scored four points and Allen made a 3-pointer as part of a 7-0 surge to pull the Broncs to 76-74 with 3:30 remaining. Isabell scored six points and Alihan Demir and Mojica each made 3-pointers in a 13-3 spurt from Drexel to end it.
